:27.270Z", "title": "C.B. Huntress, children Marion, Douglas, & Jack", "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/2016828287/"}], "resource": {"fulltext_file": "https://tile.loc.gov/text-services/word-coordinates-service?segment=/service/ndnp/fu/batch_fu_criser_ver02/data/sn84027621/00295865659/1920121701/0639.xml&format=alto_xml&full_text=1", "image": "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:fu:batch_fu_criser_ver02:data:sn84027621:00295865659:1920121701:0633/full/pct:3.125/0/default.jpg", "pdf": "https://tile.loc.gov/storage-services/service/ndnp/fu/batch_fu_criser_ver02/data/sn84027621/00295865659/1920121701/0639.pdf", "segment_count": 8, "url": "https://www.loc.gov/resource/sn84027621/1920-12-17/ed-1/", "word_coordinates": "https://tile.loc.gov/text-services/word-coordinates-service"}, "resources": [{"fulltext_file": "https://tile.loc.gov/text-services/word-coordinates-service?segment=/service/ndnp/fu/batch_fu_criser_ver02/data/sn84027621/00295865659/1920121701/0639.xml&format=alto_xml&full_text=1", "image": "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:fu:batch_fu_criser_ver02:data:sn84027621:00295865659:1920121701:0633/full/pct:3.125/0/default.jpg", "pdf": "https://tile.loc.gov/storage-services/service/ndnp/fu/batch_fu_criser_ver02/data/sn84027621/00295865659/1920121701/0639.pdf", "segment_count": 8, "url": "https://www.loc.gov/resource/sn84027621/1920-12-17/ed-1/", "word_coordinates": "https://tile.loc.gov/text-services/word-coordinates-service"}], "segment_id": "/service/ndnp/fu/batch_fu_criser_ver02/data/sn84027621/00295865659/1920121701/0639.xml", "segments": [{"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/resource/sn84027621/1920-12-17/ed-1/?sp=7"], "batch": ["fu_criser_ver02"], "campaigns": [], "composite_location": ["0/united states/", "1/united states/florida/", "2/united states/florida/marion/", "3/united states/florida/marion/ocala/"], "contributor": ["university of florida"], "date": "1920-12-17", "dates": ["1920-12-17"], "description": ["OCALA EVENING STAR FRIDAY DECEMBER 17 1920 Can It Be PcssiWc That There Are Kp More CbiMIess lonies in Florida For several months past Tba Childrens Home Society of Florida which iz doinga statewide and undenominational work for the orphan and home less children of the entire state providing for OVER TWELVE HUNDRED such children EACH YEAR has found it exceedingly difucub to find good family homes for its homeless children especially children frcm SIX to FIFTEEN years of age As a result its Receiving Home in Jacksonville is crowded to its utmost capacity children sleeping two on a little cot in many cases V The question therefore arisesAre there no more childless homes in Florida Are there no families who have one child who want another to be a little brother or sister Are there no more generous hearted people in the state who will perform the greatest service that can be performed on earth that of giving a good home to one or more homeless children There is no difficulty in rinding plenty of homes for wee babies and children up to five years of age but above that age it seems hard to find folks who will"], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2026-01-27T16:59:07.357Z", "group": ["ndnp/fu", "university-of-florida-awardee"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/resource/sn84027621/1920-12-17/ed-1/?sp=7", "image_url": ["https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:fu:batch_fu_criser_ver02:data:sn84027621:00295865659:1920121701:0639/full/pct:3.125/0/default.jpg#h=284&w=210", "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:fu:batch_fu_criser_ver02:data:sn84027621:00295865659:1920121701:0639/full/pct:6.25/0/default.jpg#h=569&w=420", "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:fu:batch_fu_criser_ver02:data:sn84027621:00295865659:1920121701:0639/full/pct:12.5/0/default.jpg#h=1138&w=840", "https://tile.loc.gov/text-services/word-coordinates-service?segment=/service/ndnp/fu/batch_fu_criser_ver02/data/sn84027621/0029586565